>did the ending first

Ah, the mystery tactic. Not a bad way to go for most stuff, really. Thanks to word processors, we can write completely disjointed chunks of ideas and eventually link them all together. I do it too, but sort of chapter by chapter; I'll have one scene, then later another scene, and then fill in between them once I'm satisfied with how the more important scenes worked out. I find it helps to do the parts I have a current yearning to do, and then consider what links it all up over the next couple of days.
I don't get a ton of time to write, but I do get a bunch of time to think, and that's about half the job right there.
